data: Pharoah Thutmose III successfully expanded the borders of the Egyptian empire through persistent military campaigns and improved military technology, such as spear tips made of titanium.
Titanium was not used in ancient times; its widespread use in materials science dates back to the 20th century.
Catherine the Great waltzed with the Qianlong Emperor at Catherine Palace.
Catherine the Great and the Qianlong Emperor never met; their reigns in Russia and China, respectively, did not overlap geographically.
